1
00:00:03,680 --> 00:00:09,020
Chief Detective 1958

2
00:00:10,940 --> 00:00:12,000
This series is unrelated to any places,
persons, settings or events.

3
00:00:12,030 --> 00:00:13,630
Scenes involving animals were filmed in
compliance with animal welfare guidelines.

4
00:00:13,650 --> 00:00:16,200
"Episode 5"

5
00:00:16,280 --> 00:00:18,200
Why are you all white as ghosts?

6
00:00:18,280 --> 00:00:20,490
What's with the makeup?

7
00:00:20,580 --> 00:00:24,040
These guys threw ash at us
as they ran away.

8
00:00:25,710 --> 00:00:28,540
Why don't you all hit the shower first?

9
00:00:29,250 --> 00:00:30,750
You all look nasty.

10
00:00:33,050 --> 00:00:36,720
Well, let me shake this off
before I go shower.

11
00:00:37,720 --> 00:00:39,680
- Let me join in.
- Go away!

12
00:00:39,760 --> 00:00:40,970
Hey, stop!

13
00:00:41,050 --> 00:00:42,220
Come on, seriously.

14
00:00:43,390 --> 00:00:45,020
- I told you to stop!
- Mister.

15
00:00:45,680 --> 00:00:46,690
Geumok.

16
00:00:47,270 --> 00:00:49,940
Sungchil…

17
00:01:50,040 --> 00:01:53,540
Is it really Sungchil?

18
00:02:09,390 --> 00:02:10,520
Take her with you.

19
00:02:11,810 --> 00:02:12,850
Sungchil…

20
00:02:17,070 --> 00:02:18,110
Any witnesses?

21
00:02:18,780 --> 00:02:20,570
No one claims to have seen anything

22
00:02:20,650 --> 00:02:22,360
before his grandmother
discovered the body.

23
00:02:24,370 --> 00:02:25,620
No one, my foot.

24
00:02:27,370 --> 00:02:28,700
They're just afraid to talk.

25
00:02:37,800 --> 00:02:40,170
We'll help you if anything happens.

26
00:02:40,970 --> 00:02:42,010
So please trust us

27
00:02:42,590 --> 00:02:43,760
and tell us what you know.

28
00:02:43,840 --> 00:02:46,180
I really wish I could,

29
00:02:47,100 --> 00:02:48,810
but you know how things are.

30
00:02:48,890 --> 00:02:50,810
And I have Geumok to take care of.

31
00:02:51,480 --> 00:02:53,440
Please come out and talk to us.

32
00:02:54,020 --> 00:02:55,560
Sir, please.

33
00:02:55,650 --> 00:02:59,110
Help us catch whoever killed Sungchil.

34
00:02:59,190 --> 00:03:00,740
What on earth happened?

35
00:03:00,820 --> 00:03:03,280
I don't know.
Just have a bowl of noodles and go.

36
00:03:06,870 --> 00:03:08,410
Do you really not know anything?

37
00:03:10,250 --> 00:03:11,290
I don't.

38
00:03:11,370 --> 00:03:12,870
Don't ask me again.

39
00:03:14,750 --> 00:03:16,460
Sungchil is dead!

40
00:03:16,540 --> 00:03:19,000
He was stabbed to death by a random punk!

41
00:03:20,010 --> 00:03:21,880
You need to speak up,

42
00:03:21,970 --> 00:03:24,300
so I can go catch or kill that prick!

43
00:03:27,800 --> 00:03:29,000
Detective Park.

44
00:03:32,060 --> 00:03:33,850
I'm begging you.

45
00:03:34,890 --> 00:03:36,060
Please stop.

46
00:03:36,860 --> 00:03:39,360
Why won't anyone talk to us?

47
00:03:40,320 --> 00:03:42,030
How could they be like this?

48
00:03:45,280 --> 00:03:46,870
They're fearing for their lives.

49
00:03:46,950 --> 00:03:48,370
Fearing who, exactly?

50
00:03:48,950 --> 00:03:52,450
Who do you think
the market merchants are most afraid of?

51
00:03:53,040 --> 00:03:54,080
You're right.

52
00:04:00,000 --> 00:04:01,800
I'm sure he did it.

53
00:04:02,380 --> 00:04:05,380
<i>If one of his thugs
hadn't stopped him then,</i>

54
00:04:05,470 --> 00:04:08,470
<i>he would've killed Sungchil
then and there.</i>

55
00:04:09,050 --> 00:04:11,350
Please don't resent
the market merchants too much.

56
00:04:12,470 --> 00:04:15,440
They want to tell you what they know,
but they're just too afraid.

57
00:04:16,980 --> 00:04:17,980
You're right.

58
00:04:18,980 --> 00:04:20,520
It's not their fault.

59
00:04:32,410 --> 00:04:36,460
Episode 5
There's No Criminal That Can't Be Caught!

60
00:04:38,750 --> 00:04:39,920
What was that?

61
00:04:40,670 --> 00:04:41,670
Go out and check.

62
00:04:45,760 --> 00:04:47,430
Move it, move it! Hurry!

63
00:04:48,010 --> 00:04:49,970
What kind of crazy punk
dares to come here?

64
00:04:55,230 --> 00:04:56,680
Come on! Go and get them!

65
00:05:12,580 --> 00:05:15,120
- Go and tell him now!
- Yes, sir.

66
00:05:20,040 --> 00:05:23,340
- The cops from Hwangchun are here.
- Who?

67
00:05:23,420 --> 00:05:24,550
The Hwangchun cops, boss.

68
00:05:25,710 --> 00:05:28,010
Does that Hwangchun prick
have a death wish?

69
00:06:08,340 --> 00:06:09,880
- Let go!
- Damn it!

70
00:06:10,720 --> 00:06:11,840
You're dead to me!

71
00:06:19,680 --> 00:06:20,890
Yeonghan, are you all right?

72
00:06:20,980 --> 00:06:21,980
Yeah.

73
00:06:34,870 --> 00:06:37,120
What's wrong with you?
Why are you even here?

74
00:06:37,200 --> 00:06:39,660
Hey, I have a favor to ask.

75
00:06:40,660 --> 00:06:41,960
Punch me.

76
00:06:43,880 --> 00:06:45,500
Are you out of your mind?

77
00:06:45,590 --> 00:06:48,590
I just want to know
how strong your punch is.

78
00:06:49,800 --> 00:06:51,220
So go ahead.

79
00:06:51,300 --> 00:06:53,680
Why? You think I won't hit you?

80
00:06:53,760 --> 00:06:55,470
Do it then.

81
00:06:57,680 --> 00:07:00,480
You better hit hard.
I don't want you to regret it.

82
00:07:00,560 --> 00:07:03,560
Clench your jaw
if you don't want to lose a tooth.

83
00:07:10,530 --> 00:07:12,570
Happy?

84
00:07:14,320 --> 00:07:17,780
- Look, you punched first, all right?
- What?

85
00:07:18,370 --> 00:07:19,740
Now, this is self-defense.

86
00:08:47,790 --> 00:08:48,790
One.

87
00:08:49,670 --> 00:08:50,710
Two.

88
00:08:50,790 --> 00:08:51,790
Three.

89
00:08:52,210 --> 00:08:53,210
Four.

90
00:09:17,650 --> 00:09:18,860
Where's the knife?

91
00:09:19,450 --> 00:09:20,450
What knife?

92
00:09:21,200 --> 00:09:23,030
The one you guys used to kill Sungchil.

93
00:09:26,950 --> 00:09:29,460
I have no idea what you're talking about.

94
00:09:34,380 --> 00:09:35,510
There's nothing.

95
00:09:38,470 --> 00:09:40,260
Search their pockets.

96
00:09:40,340 --> 00:09:41,340
Yes, sir.

97
00:09:49,890 --> 00:09:51,350
What's this?

98
00:09:56,360 --> 00:09:58,280
Since when do thugs listen
to fortune tellers?

99
00:09:59,650 --> 00:10:01,030
No, I'll suffer bad luck!

100
00:10:01,860 --> 00:10:03,120
I mean…

101
00:10:03,200 --> 00:10:04,920
p-please give it back.

102
00:10:04,950 --> 00:10:06,410
Suffer bad luck?

103
00:10:06,490 --> 00:10:08,790
You're nothing but bad luck, you snake.

104
00:10:16,130 --> 00:10:18,550
- Let's take Viper with us.
- All right.

105
00:10:19,630 --> 00:10:20,630
Get him up.

106
00:10:20,720 --> 00:10:21,940
I apologize, Chairman Lee.

107
00:10:21,970 --> 00:10:24,180
I warned you all
not to cause trouble again.

108
00:10:26,510 --> 00:10:27,930
Tell me straight.

109
00:10:30,270 --> 00:10:31,730
Did Viper do it?

110
00:10:33,350 --> 00:10:34,440
Well…

111
00:10:37,980 --> 00:10:38,990
Now,

112
00:10:40,490 --> 00:10:42,160
who did you say arrested him?

113
00:10:44,280 --> 00:10:47,660
Hey, hey, hey. You should take him
to the hospital, not bring him here.

114
00:10:47,740 --> 00:10:49,160
You mind your own business, Hwang.

115
00:10:49,660 --> 00:10:50,660
What?

116
00:10:51,660 --> 00:10:53,100
Mind your own business, you prick!

117
00:10:53,120 --> 00:10:54,330
That's enough!

118
00:10:54,920 --> 00:10:56,340
What's going on here?

119
00:10:56,420 --> 00:10:57,590
We're investigating.

120
00:10:57,960 --> 00:10:59,090
Go on.

121
00:11:02,760 --> 00:11:03,800
Why did you kill him?

122
00:11:04,970 --> 00:11:05,970
Who?

123
00:11:08,010 --> 00:11:09,890
Why did you kill Sungchil?

124
00:11:09,970 --> 00:11:11,600
Who even is Sungchil?

125
00:11:12,100 --> 00:11:13,940
I can't kill someone I don't know.

126
00:11:16,690 --> 00:11:18,020
Sungchil was a poor kid

127
00:11:18,860 --> 00:11:21,150
who was orphaned in the war.

128
00:11:21,900 --> 00:11:25,410
He just recently learned how to read
and helped his grandma read the papers.

129
00:11:25,870 --> 00:11:28,620
All he wanted was to live his life.

130
00:11:29,990 --> 00:11:32,500
Why would you kill such a kid?

131
00:11:33,000 --> 00:11:34,790
Why? Why?

132
00:11:34,870 --> 00:11:37,670
Who gives a damn about that kid?

133
00:11:47,430 --> 00:11:49,060
- Wait.
- Wait, stop, Detective Park.

134
00:11:50,850 --> 00:11:52,310
Tell me. Why did you kill him?

135
00:11:54,060 --> 00:11:56,060
I know you killed him.

136
00:11:56,150 --> 00:11:57,230
It was you, wasn't it?

137
00:11:57,310 --> 00:12:00,070
I killed him, all right?
Just put the gun down.

138
00:12:00,150 --> 00:12:02,900
So why? Why did you kill him?

139
00:12:02,990 --> 00:12:04,570
Detective Park, put down the gun first.

140
00:12:04,650 --> 00:12:08,120
Tell me, you prick. Why did you kill him?

141
00:12:08,200 --> 00:12:10,240
Tell me, you damn prick. Say it!

142
00:12:10,330 --> 00:12:12,430
You cops can't just take people like this!

143
00:12:12,450 --> 00:12:14,370
Our boss was with us drinking all night!

144
00:12:15,120 --> 00:12:17,120
This is an abuse of power.

145
00:12:17,750 --> 00:12:21,380
You cops can't just arrest people
like this without evidence.

146
00:12:21,460 --> 00:12:24,300
Boss, you drank with us all night!

147
00:12:24,380 --> 00:12:27,890
You beat up an innocent man
and held a gun to his head.

148
00:12:28,470 --> 00:12:30,640
You guys are all hopeless, aren't you?

149
00:12:30,720 --> 00:12:32,220
An innocent man, sir?

150
00:12:33,270 --> 00:12:35,270
He's the culprit who killed Sungchil.

151
00:12:35,350 --> 00:12:36,560
Do you have proof?

152
00:12:37,600 --> 00:12:38,900
He has 20 witnesses.

153
00:12:39,560 --> 00:12:41,240
I've had it up to here with you all.

154
00:12:42,570 --> 00:12:45,490
Chief Yu, I'm docking your pay
for two months.

155
00:12:46,450 --> 00:12:47,450
The rest of you

156
00:12:47,530 --> 00:12:48,950
are relieved of your duties.

157
00:12:50,320 --> 00:12:51,330
Dismissed.

158
00:12:51,910 --> 00:12:52,910
Sir?

159
00:12:55,290 --> 00:12:56,620
Give us a moment.

160
00:13:02,590 --> 00:13:04,270
What's with all the long faces?

161
00:13:05,630 --> 00:13:07,800
Don't worry. You all aren't fired.

162
00:13:08,430 --> 00:13:09,430
What about the case, sir?

163
00:13:11,300 --> 00:13:13,640
We can investigate,
but just not the Dongdaemun guys.

164
00:13:13,720 --> 00:13:15,680
That means we can't then.

165
00:13:15,770 --> 00:13:17,450
You're not going to listen to him,
are you?

166
00:13:17,890 --> 00:13:20,400
Listen to him? No, I want you
to arrest everyone responsible.

167
00:13:21,560 --> 00:13:23,150
How do we get the damn prick?

168
00:13:23,230 --> 00:13:24,570
We need to find evidence first.

169
00:13:25,280 --> 00:13:26,630
Let's start from the top.

170
00:13:26,650 --> 00:13:28,070
And where's that?

171
00:13:31,200 --> 00:13:32,280
The crime scene.

172
00:13:56,060 --> 00:13:57,100
What is it?

173
00:14:00,270 --> 00:14:02,060
It's caustic soda.

174
00:14:03,480 --> 00:14:04,880
The scene is such a mess.

175
00:14:04,940 --> 00:14:06,570
Would there still be evidence?

176
00:14:44,940 --> 00:14:45,940
Detective.

177
00:14:49,320 --> 00:14:50,900
Thank you so much.

178
00:15:09,260 --> 00:15:10,260
Let's go.

179
00:15:23,310 --> 00:15:27,110
<i>♪ The seagulls cry so sorrowfully ♪</i>

180
00:15:27,190 --> 00:15:29,360
<i>♪ At the Incheon port of farewell ♪</i>

181
00:15:29,440 --> 00:15:31,170
- You sound great.
- I love it.

182
00:15:31,190 --> 00:15:34,950
<i>♪ The sailors in love shed their tears ♪</i>

183
00:15:35,030 --> 00:15:38,780
<i>♪ At every port ♪</i>

184
00:15:38,870 --> 00:15:42,620
<i>♪ Just as they have fallen in love ♪</i>

185
00:15:42,710 --> 00:15:44,710
<i>♪ The boat horn of farewell cries out ♪</i>

186
00:15:44,790 --> 00:15:46,310
Isn't that nice!

187
00:16:32,090 --> 00:16:33,920
Come on, stop crying.

188
00:16:34,010 --> 00:16:36,180
I promise you
I'll arrest Viper within three days.

189
00:16:36,930 --> 00:16:40,510
You don't have any evidence.
You don't even have the murder weapon.

190
00:16:40,600 --> 00:16:43,020
Then we'll go find the weapon, right?

191
00:16:43,100 --> 00:16:45,680
It'll be hard to find
if they hid it really well.

192
00:16:45,770 --> 00:16:47,350
Come on, you…

193
00:16:49,020 --> 00:16:51,400
All we have left is Sungchil.

194
00:16:51,480 --> 00:16:54,820
We have to stay on high alert.
At this rate, we'll lose Viper.

195
00:16:55,990 --> 00:16:58,240
But can't Sungchil…

196
00:16:59,660 --> 00:17:04,910
Can't he have an autopsy done on him?

197
00:17:06,040 --> 00:17:09,460
I read about it
in American mystery novels.

198
00:17:09,540 --> 00:17:10,790
We could do it,

199
00:17:11,790 --> 00:17:13,340
but it's not like the books.

200
00:17:13,420 --> 00:17:15,550
It won't directly tell us who killed him.

201
00:17:16,260 --> 00:17:18,840
I observed an autopsy once,
and it wasn't that helpful.

202
00:17:19,340 --> 00:17:22,350
Should we still have it done just in case?

203
00:17:22,970 --> 00:17:25,810
Never mind it.
It'll just hurt his grandmother even more.

204
00:17:28,230 --> 00:17:29,560
Let's convince her

205
00:17:30,190 --> 00:17:31,190
and have it done.

206
00:17:32,230 --> 00:17:34,150
- What?
- Like I said,

207
00:17:34,230 --> 00:17:36,820
all we have left is Sungchil's body.

208
00:17:39,240 --> 00:17:40,240
Ma'am.

209
00:17:42,490 --> 00:17:44,450
There's this thing called an autopsy.

210
00:17:46,620 --> 00:17:48,830
It may help us find out…

211
00:17:50,080 --> 00:17:53,960
It may help find out how Sungchil died.

212
00:17:54,670 --> 00:17:58,420
And to do that,
we'll have to look inside his body.

213
00:18:01,180 --> 00:18:03,180
You don't need to agree if it's too much.

214
00:18:03,260 --> 00:18:04,680
We won't do it if you say no.

215
00:18:04,760 --> 00:18:08,100
You don't have to agree to it
if it upsets you, ma'am.

216
00:18:11,770 --> 00:18:12,770
Get it done.

217
00:18:16,070 --> 00:18:18,150
If it'll help catch his killer,

218
00:18:18,900 --> 00:18:19,990
it must be done.

219
00:18:22,110 --> 00:18:23,240
Thank you.

220
00:18:25,330 --> 00:18:27,290
I promise you I'll catch his murderer.

221
00:18:29,370 --> 00:18:30,500
That's a promise.

222
00:18:36,050 --> 00:18:39,880
Thank you for telling me
that you'll stop at nothing.

223
00:18:41,550 --> 00:18:42,930
I cannot thank you enough.

224
00:19:02,910 --> 00:19:05,870
National Forensic Service

225
00:19:13,580 --> 00:19:15,540
The body reveals the truth

226
00:19:15,630 --> 00:19:17,190
We found a total of eight stab wounds.

227
00:19:17,210 --> 00:19:20,760
The cause of death is likely
excessive bleeding from the wounds.

228
00:19:22,010 --> 00:19:26,220
I must say, I've never seen
a more brutal death in my career.

229
00:19:29,220 --> 00:19:31,890
Whoever stabbed him
must have suffered injuries on their hand.

230
00:19:33,940 --> 00:19:35,650
No, I'll suffer bad luck!

231
00:19:35,730 --> 00:19:38,190
You're nothing but bad luck, you snake.

232
00:19:42,490 --> 00:19:44,860
The width and depth
of the blade are worth noting

233
00:19:44,950 --> 00:19:47,870
as the wounds are very narrow and long.

234
00:19:47,950 --> 00:19:51,330
This suggests
that the weapon wasn't an ordinary knife.

235
00:19:51,830 --> 00:19:53,000
Look here.

236
00:19:54,500 --> 00:19:55,580
And here.

237
00:19:56,290 --> 00:19:58,460
There are also bruises.

238
00:19:59,170 --> 00:20:02,670
Those bruises
can't have been caused by impact.

239
00:20:03,470 --> 00:20:05,350
Those are what you see in wrestling

240
00:20:05,380 --> 00:20:06,890
when the thigh bands are too tight.

241
00:20:15,140 --> 00:20:17,000
- Stand still, Detective Kim.
- All right.

242
00:20:17,020 --> 00:20:19,060
Grab his arm and pull,
Detective Jo.

243
00:20:19,150 --> 00:20:20,150
Okay.

244
00:20:24,530 --> 00:20:26,010
There were at least three.

245
00:20:26,070 --> 00:20:27,160
One guy stabbed him,

246
00:20:27,740 --> 00:20:29,030
and two held him still.

247
00:20:29,120 --> 00:20:31,540
Do you see this reddish part?

248
00:20:32,120 --> 00:20:33,200
It's some sort of rash.

249
00:20:33,700 --> 00:20:36,170
It looks like a burn wound
but not an ordinary one.

250
00:20:37,370 --> 00:20:38,380
Perhaps from chemicals?

251
00:20:39,000 --> 00:20:41,760
Wait, we found caustic soda
in the water at the crime scene.

252
00:20:42,130 --> 00:20:44,210
Caustic soda could cause a burn like this.

253
00:20:45,760 --> 00:20:48,180
We'll end the external examination here

254
00:20:48,640 --> 00:20:50,320
and proceed with the internal examination.

255
00:21:10,910 --> 00:21:12,580
I'll pray for you…

256
00:21:13,620 --> 00:21:15,580
that you be born into…

257
00:21:16,620 --> 00:21:18,540
a good, wealthy family…

258
00:21:19,540 --> 00:21:21,380
in your next life, Sungchil.

259
00:21:22,750 --> 00:21:25,460
Don't even pretend to know me…

260
00:21:26,920 --> 00:21:27,930
all right?

261
00:21:28,680 --> 00:21:29,890
Ma'am…

262
00:21:32,510 --> 00:21:37,770
You won't have to care about spelling
where you are now.

263
00:21:42,310 --> 00:21:44,400
I hope you're free and happy there.

264
00:21:44,480 --> 00:21:45,650
Elementary Korean

265
00:21:47,400 --> 00:21:49,530
I brought you new shoes…

266
00:21:51,200 --> 00:21:52,370
for your journey.

267
00:22:04,880 --> 00:22:07,710
Sungchil!

268
00:22:13,350 --> 00:22:16,680
Sungchil!

269
